

The key CSS code is as follows:

.article-body {
width:100%!important
}


More completely, here's the full CSS code I'm using for the timeline here (http://www.bostonglobe.com/2014/10/21/blackstone-home-where-infants-bodies-found-being-torn-down/YvoMdFpk7g5HPudXctwuSL/igraphic.html?p1=Article_Graphic) that is full width:

<style type="text/css">
 
.article-body {
width:100%!important
}
 
.section-nav {
    display: none;
}
 
div.article {
    width: 100%;
    margin: 0;
}
 
.aside {
    display: none;
}
 
.interactive-body {
    float: left;
    width: 100%;
}
 
 
</style>
